<collectingCountry box="[668,767,1377,1403]" name="Portugal" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Portugal</collectingCountry>
: all 11 provinces (see also 
<bibRefCitation author="Naglis, S. &amp; Bartak, M." box="[1072,1325,1376,1403]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" pagination="125 - 137" refId="ref33294" refString="Naglis, S. &amp; Bartak, M. (2015) Dolichopodidae (Diptera) from the Iberian Peninsula, with description of three new species. Zootaxa, 3964 (1), 125 - 137. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3964.1.9" type="journal article" year="2015">Naglis &amp; Barták 2015</bibRefCitation>
, Dyte unpubl. data).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="33.[151,1437,1340,1619]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,300,1449,1475]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Ecology.</emphasis>
This species is distributed rather evenly over all macrohabitat categories, with a slightly lower representation in dunes, and a higher one in grasslands and heathlands. Its ecological profile in northwestern Europe is not well defined as here the species has been found in a variety of biotopes too.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="33.[151,1437,1340,1619]" box="[199,701,1556,1583]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,1556,1583]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Rarity (%).</emphasis>
